<P>
   FIRSTUNION-MARKETPLACE (Undated) _ First Union Corp., a megabank
created through pricey, rapid-fire acquisitions, stunned investors
and employees Tuesday when it warned that profits for the second
quarter and the year would fall far below previous estimates. It
was the second time this year that the bank has had to revise its
1999 earnings estimates sharply downward, leaving its credibility
in tatters, its financial outlook clouded and its ability to remain
independent severely impaired. By Timothy L. O'Brien.
</P>
