   ILLUSTRATED-BIBLE (West Hatfield, Mass.) _ The artist Barry
Moser is working at his home here on a task that recalls a much
earlier era, creating hundreds of images to illustrate every book
of the Bible, from Creation to Apocalypse. Since early 1996 Moser,
who is widely known as an illustrator of children's books and
classics, has devoted each day to working on what will total 231
engravings for an unusual edition of the King James Version of the
Bible. By Gustav Niebuhr. (1850 words)
