<P>
   LIFESTYLE
</P>
<P>
   WRESTLING-RATINGS _ The death Sunday night of World Wrestling
federation wrestley Owen Hart has brought reality tumbling down on
a business where faked mayhem and outrageous stunts have become the
norm and driven cable TV ratings sky high. (Scott, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   EDs _ A Knight Ridder Tribune graphic is available to go with
this story.
</P>
<P>
   FAT-MANHEIM _ She's fat. No, we're not being mean. Just
cooperative. Camryn Manheim may be an Emmy and Golden Globe-winning
actress for TV's ``The Practice'' but it's her weight that's
front-and-center in everyone's minds, largely thanks to her. First
she yelled ``This is for all the fat girls!'' in picking up her
Emmy last fall; now she's turned her successful one-woman stage
show ``Wake Up, I'm Fat!'' into a book of the same name. On
Wednesday evening, Manheim took over Lane Bryant at Kennesaw's Town
Center Mall for a booksigning and general lovefest with fans of her
no-nonsense, no-apologies style. (Vejnoska, Atlanta
ournal-Constitution). 15.
</P>
<P>
   MIDLIFE-JOURNEY _ ALVA, WYOMING _ My reader-inspired West Palm
Beach, Fla.-to-Alaska road trip included a western swing into
Canada that forced me to choose between: 1. The revolting banana
slugs of the Pacific Northwest (suggested by Carol Buetens of
Stuart, Fla.) and 2. The insidious blood-sucking leeches of the
Mahoney ranch in eastern Wyoming. It couldn't be both. (EDS: This
is Installment 12 on Ron Wiggins' midlife journey to Mount
McKinley.) (Wiggins, Palm Beach Post) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   COUPLES _ WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ What makes a good couple?
Charles T. Hill has the ivory-tower proof. The psychology professor
at Whittier College in Whittier, Calif., tracked dating couples
over a two-year period, and later followed 231 married couples for
15 years. He found that not only did the daters pair off with
people of similar attractiveness, but also that looks often helped
determine a relationship's longevity. ``The couples that stayed
together tended to be better matched than those who broke up,'' he
says. (Sturrock, Palm Beach Post) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   NEWS-QUESTIONS _ Q&AMP;A on the news, in two takes. (Bessonnette,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution) (l, a) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   FOOD
</P>
<P>
   COXNET FOOD PAGE
