<P>
   COXNET FOOD 0525 _ Spring is luring us from our dinner tables to
the porch, the back yard, the park and the lakeside for fresh-air
dining. But when something more elegant is in order, we borrow from
the French to suggest pates and terrines. (Walker, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) Art includes one 4-column color photo of
Asparagus and Shiitake Mushroom Terrine and Ham and Zucchini
Terrine.
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   RECIPES _ Asparagus and Shiitake Mushroom Terrine, Ham and
Zucchini Terrine and Feta Pasta Primavera.
</P>
<P>
   CYBERSPICE _ Potluck or covered dish dinners have been part of
the American scene since the Pilgrims and their Native American
neighbors sat down together for that first Thanksgiving. Various
Web sites show how potluck parties meld beautifully with today's
lifetstyles. (Parham, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   FOOD-BURGERS _ Burgers for Memorial Day don't have to be
boring....we not only tell you how to enliven the usual ground beef
but also offer alternatives using lamb, chichen, turkey and
chickpeas with condiments to match. (Walker, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) WITH COLOR PHOTO
</P>
