<P>
   MURRAY-COLUMN _ My father's family had a small farm in
Louisiana, but when he and my mother married, he went to work for a
lumber company for a dollar a day. We lived in a two-room cabin
that could be put on a railroad flatcar and easily moved through
the Louisiana forests as my father's job moved. I guess that would
be called an employee benefit today. Yes, my father's job was to
cut down those beautiful long leaf pine trees. There is no way I
can fully describe those pine woods of my childhood, how beautiful
they were. (Hestand, Cox News Service). MOVED.
