comparing Thomas Jefferson's plight to that of womanizers a
sacrilege. After all, he was a widower, and his property, the slave
Sally Hemings, was half-sister to his deceased wife and said to be
so much like her they could have been twins. Whatever. Like lesser
men, Jefferson apparently made private choices he knew to be
inconsistent with public morality. He lived a lie. (Jefferson, Palm
Beach Post) MOVED.
