   FOOD-IMPROMPTU _ Impromptu, casual , carefree. Pick your colors,
use things you have around your home, decorate around them. Serve
take-out or home cooked food. But keep it simple, refreshing and
fun. Sue Smith is a master at such spur-of-the-moment parties.
Running to the store and gathering up olives, cheeses, breads.
Marinating fresh fruits with liqueurs and freezing them in a loaf
for festive, icy slicing. Scatter a few fern fronds on top and she
has an easy attractive table. Siders on two or three other local
impromptu entertainers. (Crider, Austin American-Statesman). WITH
PHOTOS.
