</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-VIDEO-MINIS27-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Mini reviews of recently released videos
 &HT;    By Eleanor Ringel Gillespie, Steve Murray and Phil Kloer
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service  ``Theory of Flight'' (R) _ Doesn't
<TEXT>
soar as it could, but the two leads keep it aloft with their
marvelous acting. Kenneth Branagh is an artist/dreamer/inventor
whose shenanigans earn him 120 hours of community service.
Specifically, caring for a cantankerous young woman (Helena Bonham
Carter) with Lou Gehrig's disease. Lots of '60s whimsy and
symbolism here, but the stars' expertise is enough to make the
pluses far outweigh the minuses. Grade: B
<P>
   _ Eleanor Ringel Gillespie
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  ``Insomnia'' (unrated) _ In this twisty Scandinavian thriller,
Stellan Skarsgard plays a detective chasing a serial killer. The
endless summer nights, when the sun never sets, are already putting
him on edge. But when he accidentally shoots a fellow officer and
tries to peg it on the elusive killer, a dangerous game of
cat-and-mouse begins. With subtitles. Grade: B
</P>
<P>
   _ Steve Murray
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  ``Alice in Wonderland'' (unrated) _ The sets are fantastic,
and the costumes are more fantastic than the sets, and the
computer-generated creatures from Jim Henson's shop are the best of
all.
</P>
<P>
   The star power is impressive: Whoopi Goldberg as the Cheshire
Cat, Miranda Richardson as the Queen of Hearts, Martin Short as the
Mad Hatter, Ben Kingsley as the Caterpillar, and Gene Wilder,
George Wendt, Peter Ustinov and others along for the ride.
</P>
<P>
   And an hour into it, you'll be checking your watch more often
than the March Hare, wondering if this movie is lasting three hours
or three weeks. Grade: C-
</P>
<P>
   _ Phil Kloer
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  ``Un Air de Famille'' (unrated) _ A comedy-drama about the
love-hate dynamics of family, this beautifully acted movie takes
place almost entirely in a family-owned cafe run by Henri
(Jean-Pierre Bacri), the sibling who's been assigned the role of
the clan's failure.
</P>
<P>
   His brother Philippe (Wladimir Yordanoff) is a bigwig at a
computer firm, where their sister Betty (Agnes Jaoui) also works.
</P>
<P>
   Gathering to celebrate the birthday of Philippe's
suburban-Barbie wife Yolande (Catherine Frot), the family (headed
by the demanding mother, played by Claire Maurier) falls instantly
into old patterns.
</P>
<P>
   Grade: B
</P>
<P>
   _ Steve Murray
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
