<P>
   MASS-MOCA (North Adams, Mass.) _ There is likely to be a
collective sigh of relief in this corner of the Berkshires on
Sunday with the opening of the $37 million Massachusetts Museum of
Contemporary Art after 13 roller-coaster years and a last-minute
scramble to install the giant artworks it was designed to display.
MASS MoCA, as the center has become known, is a marriage of art and
urban renewal dogged by politics, economic constraints and
uncertain artistic ambitions. By Carol Vogel.
</P>
<P>
   SC-BOOKS (Spartanburg, S.C.) _ Arts in America: The robust
literary scene in Spartanburg, S.C. By Peter Applebome.
</P>
<P>
   BOOK-TALK (Undated) _ The weekly book column. By Martin Arnold.
</P>
<P>
   SOUL-BOOK-REVIEW (Undated) _ ``Jewish Soul, American Beat'':
Barbara Pfeffer, director; a documentary. Reviewed by Lawrence Van
Gelder.
</P>
<P>
   HAVANA-BOOK-REVIEW (Undated) _ ``Havana Bay,'' by Martin Cruz
Smith (Random House). Reviewed by Christopher Lehmann-Haupt.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; SPORTS &LR;  (``s'' code)
</P>
<P>
   BBA-ANDERSON-COLUMN (New York) _ Sports of The Times column on
the Yanks-Boston, game. By Dave Anderson.
</P>
<P>
   BKN-BERKOW-COLUMN (New York) _ Sports of The Times column on the
Knicks and Latrell Sprewell. By Ira Berkow.
</P>
<P>
   BBA-YANKS-BOSOX (New York) _ N.Y. Yankees host the Boston Red
Sox, 1:05 p.m. ET start. By Buster Olney.
</P>
<P>
   BBN-METS-PIRATES (Pittsburgh) _ N.Y. Mets at the Pirates, 7:35
p.m. ET start. By Jason Diamos.
</P>
<P>
   RAC-BELMONT (New York) _ Silverbutlletday will run in the
Belmont after all, setting up a terrific race on June 5.
Charismatic will be going for the Triple Crown and Silverbulletday,
the best filly in the country, will be trying to stop him. By
Joseph Durso.
</P>
<P>
   TEN-FRENCH-OPEN (Paris) _ Action at the French Open, including
the second-round ouster of Kafelnikov. By Robin Finn.
</P>
