<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-TV-SWEEPS-SFCHRON </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
CHEST-BEATING FOR SWEEPS MONTH 
</HEADLINE>
   By JOHN CARMAN  
 c.1999, San Francisco Chronicle  
<TEXT>
<P>
   The May sweeps end Wednesday night, but not before ``Cleopatra''
leads the way to one of TV's all-time breast months. And:
</P>
<P>
   _ &LR;   &LR; On a special classic TV installment of ``Hollywood
Squares,'' Jerry Mathers, as the Beaver. And (set ital)still(end
ital) Whoopi Goldberg got the center square.
</P>
<P>
   _ &LR;   &LR; ``Hard Copy'' asked, ``Is bigger better?'' More and more
Hollywood actresses, it said, are downsizing their breasts.
</P>
<P>
   _ &LR;   &LR; The very next day on ``Hard Copy'': the benefits of breast
enlargement pills.
</P>
<P>
   _ &LR;   &LR; Ricki Lake's high points: ``We Had a Threesome, but Today
One of You Gets the Boot,'' and ``I'm a Queen in Drag, I've Gotta
Make Over My Friend Who's a Hag.''
</P>
<P>
   _ &LR;   &LR; UPN aired a ``Star Wars'' takeoff in which all the
characters were played by human thumbs. All in all, it was a more
satisfying film than ``Star Wars: Episode I _ The Phantom Menace.''
</P>
<P>
   _ &LR;   &LR; Huge month for ``Extra,'' including a report about Jennifer
Briggs, a sixth-grade teacher from North Carolina who had her legal
name changed to Obi-Wan Kenobi. She should have seen the movie
first.
</P>
<P>
   _ &LR;   &LR; On ``World's Most Dangerous Magic II,'' a woman was manacled
and sealed in a coffin with 125 live rats, none of which was a
relative.
</P>
<P>
   _ &LR;   &LR; What a month for Jenny Jones. First a jury finds her show
liable for the death of a guest five years ago. Then, ``Stripper
Makeovers.''
</P>
<P>
   _ &LR;   &LR; Also on ``Jenny Jones,'' a show devoted to huge-breasted
women. Sadly, they can't sleep on their bellies. But one told Jenny
she gets free lawn care, and another enjoys free bean burritos at
Taco Bell.
</P>
<P>
   _ &LR;   &LR; Stuntman Robbie Knievel required two live Fox specials to do
it, but he jumped the Grand Canyon west chasm on his motorcycle.
The post-jump medical report _ two broken ribs and a sprained
ankle.
</P>
<P>
   _ &LR;   &LR; On ``The Jerry Springer Show,'' two volunteers from the
audience helped a bare-breasted stripper, Jenna, demonstrate her
``banana split special'' in a plastic wading pool. The volunteers
were forced to split when Jenna's boyfriend stormed onto the set,
throwing punches.
</P>
<P>
   _ &LR;   &LR; Heifers on the highway: ``Hard Copy'' patched together a
montage of cows and pigs going crazy on American roads.
</P>
<P>
   _ &LR;   &LR; A sweeps grand slam. In one episode of ``Frasier,'' Roz,
Bulldog, Niles, Daphne, Frasier, Dad and Eddie the dog all had sex.
In Eddie's case, with a poodle.
</P>
<P>
   _ &LR;   &LR; ``Extra'' shed light on the seldom-seen world of adult
thumb-suckers. ``We're just people,'' one said. ``We just want to
be loved.''
</P>
<P>
   _ &LR;   &LR; Spreading goodwill during a family vacation to Japan, Homer
Simpson threw the emperor into a bin of thongs used in sumo
wrestling.
</P>
<P>
   _ &LR;   &LR; Michael Jordan's sister, Delores, told ``Inside Edition''
she's writing a tell-all book about the Jordan family's dirty
laundry. She also said she's puzzled that her famous brother
stopped paying her daughter's college tuition after he found out
about the book.
</P>
<P>
   _ &LR;   &LR; ``7th Heaven'' plays tough. It bumped off a family dog in an
episode called ``All Dogs Go to Heaven.'' Not to worry. It wasn't
Happy, the Camden family dog.
</P>
<P>
   _ &LR;   &LR; Finally, an ``Extra'' extra in which the show investigated
breast augmentation procedures. For men.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
