<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-KEBABS-2ndTake-TEX </SLUG>
 
UNDATED: Books, $35) 
<TEXT>
<P>
   SKEWERED SINGAPORE CHICKEN AND PINEAPPLE
</P>
<P>
   Serves 4
</P>
<P>
   3 tablespoons brown sugar
</P>
<P>
   3 tablespoons low-sodium soy sauce
</P>
<P>
   2 tablespoons pineapple juice
</P>
<P>
   4 teaspoons fresh lime juice
</P>
<P>
   2 teaspoons grated peeled fresh ginger
</P>
<P>
   2 teaspoons vegetable oil
</P>
<P>
   1 1/2 teaspoons curry powder
</P>
<P>
   1/4 teaspoon salt
</P>
<P>
   3 garlic cloves, minced
</P>
<P>
   1 pound skinned, boned chicken breast, cut into 32 bite-size
pieces
</P>
<P>
   1 cup (1-inch) pieces red bell pepper
</P>
<P>
   1 1/2 cups (1-inch) cubed fresh pineapple
</P>
<P>
   Cooking spray
</P>
<P>
   Prepare grill or broiler.
</P>
<P>
   Combine first 9 ingredients in large bowl. Add chicken and bell
pepper, tossing to coat. Thread chicken, pineapple and bell pepper
alternately onto each of 8 (12-inch skewers). Discard marinade.
Place kebabs on grill rack or broiler pan coated with cooking
spray; cook 10 minutes or until chicken is done, turning
occasionally. Serve with rice.
</P>
<P>
   Nutritional analysis per serving: 419 calories, 3 grams fat, 64
grams carbohydrates, 31 grams protein, 66 milligrams cholesterol,
332 milligrams sodium, 7 percent of calories from fat.
</P>
<P>
   _Cooking Light magazine, March 1999
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   LAMB AND TOMATO KEBABS
</P>
<P>
   Serves 4
</P>
<P>
   1 large onion, peeled
</P>
<P>
   1 large green bell pepper
</P>
<P>
   12 rib lamb chops (each about 3 ounces and 1-inch thick)
</P>
<P>
   8 fresh, ripe plum tomatoes
</P>
<P>
   1 tablespoon coarse salt
</P>
<P>
   1 teaspoon freshly ground black pepper
</P>
<P>
   1 teaspoon dried mint
</P>
<P>
   1 teaspoon dried oregano
</P>
<P>
   1 teaspoon dried rosemary
</P>
<P>
   3 tablespoons extra-virgin olive oil, or as needed, for brushing
</P>
<P>
   4 pita breads
</P>
<P>
   Cut onion into 8 wedges and break each wedge into segments. Stem
and seed bell pepper and cut into strips 1 1/2 inches long and
1/2-inch wide.
</P>
<P>
   Thread ingredients for kebabs onto skewers in following
sequence: a lamb chop, a piece of onion, a piece of bell pepper, a
tomato (skewered crosswise), a piece of onion, a piece of bell
pepper, another lamb chop, more onion and pepper, another tomato,
more onion and pepper, and another lamb chop. Run a metal skewer
through meat of each chop at a 60-degree angle to the bone. Arrange
kebabs on a platter or baking sheet, cover loosely with plastic
wrap and set aside, in refrigerator, until ready to grill.
</P>
<P>
   When ready to grill, prepare spice mixture. Combine all spices
in small bowl, crumbling rosemary between your fingers.
</P>
<P>
   Brush chops and vegetables on each skewer with oil and season
generously with spice mixture. Oil grill grate, then arrange kebabs
on hot grate and grill, turning with tongs, until lamb is cooked to
taste, about 12 minutes for medium. As kebabs cook, brush with oil
and season with more of spice mix.
</P>
<P>
   Fold pita around meat on each skewer and pull out skewer. Serve
immediately.
</P>
<P>
   Nutritional analysis per serving: 504 calories, 20 grams fat, 40
grams carbohydrates, 41 grams protein, 108 milligrams cholesterol,
1,029 milligrams sodium, 36 percent of calories from fat.
</P>
<P>
   _''The Barbecue! Bible'' by Steven Raichlen (Workman, $18.95)
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   LEMON GRASS BEEF WITH PEANUTS
</P>
<P>
   Serves 4
</P>
<P>
   1 1/2 pounds boneless beef sirloin or top round
</P>
<P>
   2 cloves garlic, peeled
</P>
<P>
   2 stalks lemon grass, trimmed and cut into 1/4-inch slices, or 2
strips lemon zest (each 2-by-1/2 inches, removed with a vegetable
peeler)
</P>
<P>
   1 tablespoon coriander seeds
</P>
<P>
   2 tablespoons firmly packed light brown sugar
</P>
<P>
   1/4 cup Asian fish sauce
</P>
<P>
   1/4 cup coarsely chopped dry-roasted peanuts, for garnish
</P>
<P>
   Lay steaks flat on cutting board and cut crosswise into long,
thin strips. Each should be about 1/8-inch thick, 1-inch wide and 4
to 5 inches long. Weave beef strips lengthwise onto skewers and set
aside in large baking dish while you prepare marinade.
</P>
<P>
   Combine garlic, lemon grass, coriander seeds and brown sugar in
mortar and pound into a coarse paste with pestle. If you don't have
a mortar and pestle, puree ingredients in a blender. Stir in fish
sauce. Drizzle marinade over beef skewers and rub it into beef,
coating as thoroughly as possible. Cover and let marinate, in
refrigerator, for 30 minutes, or until grill is ready.
</P>
<P>
   Preheat grill to high.
</P>
<P>
   When ready to cook, oil grill grate. Arrange skewers on hot
grate and grill, turning with tongs, until meat is cooked to taste,
1 to 2 minutes per side (2 to 4 minutes in all) for medium.
Sprinkle skewers with chopped peanuts and serve at once.
</P>
<P>
   Nutritional analysis per serving: 421 calories, 26 grams fat, 9
grams carbohydrates, 38 grams protein, 113 milligrams cholesterol,
374 milligrams sodium, 55 percent of calories from fat.
</P>
<P>
   _''The Barbecue! Bible''
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   GRILLED MANGO KEBABS
</P>
<P>
   Yields 10-12 skewers
</P>
<P>
   1 large mango, cubed
</P>
<P>
   1 cup pineapple chunks, drained
</P>
<P>
   2 oranges, sectioned, sections cut in half if large
</P>
<P>
   2 tablespoons honey
</P>
<P>
   1/2 cup lime juice
</P>
<P>
   Wooden skewers, soaked in water
</P>
<P>
   Dipping sauce:
</P>
<P>
   1 cup plain yogurt
</P>
<P>
   1/2 cup freshly squeezed orange juice
</P>
<P>
   Alternate cubes of pineapple, mango and orange on wooden
skewers. Brush with honey-lime juice mixture. Grill over medium
heat until pineapple is glazed brown.
</P>
<P>
   Remove and serve hot with dipping sauce.
</P>
<P>
   Nutritional analysis per serving: 69 calories, 1 gram fat, 16
grams carbohydrates, 1 gram protein, 2 milligrams cholesterol, 10
milligrams sodium, 10 percent of calories from fat.
</P>
<P>
   _Cox News Service
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
