</P>
<P>
   BKN-HAWKS _ Hawks president Stan Kasten calls this summer the
most important off-season in the history of the franchise. While
stopping short of promising major changes on the roster, he said
changes will be made and that there are no untouchables on the
team. He also expressed concerned about coach Lenny Wilkens using a
small rotation of players. He did say he was happy with the job
performances of Wilkens and GM Pete Babcock. (Denberg, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
