   TENNIS
</P>
<P>
   TEN-HALLOFFAME _ ATHENS, Ga. _ The Intercollegiate Tennis
Association will induct eight new members - six players, one coach
and one conrtibutor - to the Collegiate Tennis Hall of Fame
Wednesday at the University of Georgia. The Gullikson twins of
Northern Illinois head the inductees. Others are Pennsylvania's
Wallace Johnson, Mel Purcell of Memphis State and Tennessee,
William Scanlon of Trinity, and John Whitlinger of Stanford. The
coach inductee is Bennie Purcell of Murray State. The contributor
inductee is Charles Mapes, former coach at Baylor. (Brice Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 12.
</P>
<P>
   OLYMPICS
</P>
<P>
   OLY-RECORDS _ ATLANTA _ Atlanta Olympics officials said they
will respond early next week to a Congressional inquiry into the
city's bid for the Games. They will provide a far more detailed
response to questions about excessive gifts and visits by IOC
members to Atlanta than they offered the IOC in its own inquiry
into improprieties in candidate cities. Also, advancing Thursday's
hearing on the exchange of lawsuits by the GAAF and AJC. (Turner,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 10.
</P>
