<P>
   INTERNATIONAL
</P>
<P>
   SAFRICA-CRIME _ Violent crime in South Africa is as bad as
anywhere in the world. Almost every house, rich and poor, is
surrounded by razor wire. Armed private security guards patrol
everywhere. People carjack ambulances and rape old women. Cadres of
security guards engage in deadly shootouts with cadres of robbers.
The crime is prompting some whites to leave the country _ taking
with them their capital and their business expertise. It is also
causing people to question the competence of the ANC-led goverment,
and it has become a major political issue in the current election
campaign. (Melvin, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 30. WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
<P>
   NATIONAL
</P>
<P>
   GORE _ DALLAS _ Vice President Al Gore attends an event of
school safety with his wife, Tipper. (Shepard, Cox News Service).
25.
</P>
<P>
   Moving in (w) Washington and (p) politics categories.
</P>
<P>
   FIRES0527 _ WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ Nearly 10,000 acres of
Everglades muck continued to burn, dumping smoke in southern Palm
Beach and Broward counties Wednesday as forest rangers hooked up a
massive sprinkler system to extinguish it. Workers have to use
cranes to hoist the pumps and lines, which will snake from a canal
at the fire's northern edge. The fire started Friday as a brushfire
that spread to about 1,200 acres by Sunday. (Staletovich, Palm
Beach Post)
</P>
<P>
   OLY-RECORDS _ ATLANTA _ Atlanta Olympics officials said they
will respond early next week to a Congressional inquiry into the
city's bid for the Games. They will provide a far more detailed
response to questions about excessive gifts and visits by IOC
members to Atlanta than they offered the IOC in its own inquiry
into improprieties in candidate cities. Also, advancing Thursday's
hearing on the exchange of lawsuits by the GAAF and AJC. (Turner,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 10.
</P>
