   CASINO _ Follow-up story on plans to build a casino in metro
Atlanta. The local governent and the governor both oppose the plan,
but developers have an appeal process. (Ellis, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   BUMBLING-ROBBERS _ DAYTON, Ohio _ Compared with their romantic,
swashbuckling counterparts of the 1920s and 1930s, some of the
Dayton area's recent bank robbers are a rather disappointing lot.
These are the tales of four who got caught. In keeping with an
age-old tradition of giving daring robbers memorable handles such
as Machine Gun Kelly or the Sundance Kid, consider their new-age
counterparts _ the Gentleman Bandit, the Mutt and Jeff Robbery Duo,
and accused who might be called the Dumpster Diver. (Hills, Dayton
Daily News) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   GA-PARKS _ ATLANTA _ Thinking about spending the Memorial Day
weekend at one of Georgia's State Parks? Think again. For the first
time in the history of the system, all 2,900 campsites, 300 cabins
and 62 lodge rooms in the state's 48 parks, from the north Georgia
mountains all the way to the Okefenokee Swamp have been booked
solid for at least a week. (Mitchell, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
