A2256 &Cx1f; ttx-z
r e &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-GOSPEL-MUSIC-TEX     05-26 0306
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-GOSPEL-MUSIC-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
`LIVE IN DETROIT II' IS A SUCCESSFUL ENCORE
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By DAVE FERMAN 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   ``Live in Detroit II''
</P>
<P>
   Vickie Winans
</P>
<P>
   CGI Platinum
</P>
<P>
   Vickie Winans' 1997 CD, ``Live in Detroit,'' was a huge success
for the Motor City-based vocalist, garnering Stellar Award
nominations and a Grammy nomination for Best Female Contemporary
Soul Gospel Album.
</P>
<P>
   Considering that CD's continued success _ an astounding 98 weeks
in the top 30 of the national gospel charts, and it's currently at
26 _ a second volume may seem a bit premature.
</P>
<P>
   But a listen to ``Live in Detroit II'' dispels such a notion.
Recorded in October at Detroit's Straight Gate Church and featuring
the Straight Gate Mass Choir, ``II'' is a testimony to Winans'
powerful voice and her ability to mix traditional and modern
sounds.
</P>
<P>
   Overproduction is a common problem with modern gospel records,
and ``II'' suffers a bit, having too much sheen in some spots. But
most of the time, Winans' emphatic, roof-raising vocals and her
deft interaction with the choir more than make up for this.
</P>
<P>
   ``I Hear the Music in the Air'' kicks things off with a distinct
Latin flavor, and from there the CD alternates up-tempo material _
such as the traditional ``Already Been to the Water'' _ with
quieter stuff. Winans sings extremely well throughout. Vocal
arrangements are taut and powerful, and the medley of old gospel
songs _ ``I Know the Lord Will Make a Way, Just Another Day That
the Lord Has Kept Me, I Don't Know What I'd Do Without the Lord''
and ``I Thank the Lord Because He's Been So Good to Me'' _ provides
a welcome look back. This second live volume is Vickie Winans at
her best. .MDBU/.MDNM/ (Visit the Star-Telegram's online services
on the World Wide Web: www.star-telegram.com) &QL; 
nn
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
