of the opposition Democratic Party, has been indicted for treason
after a series of anti-war demonstrations there. The mayor, Velimir
Ilic, officially on vacation, has fled to Montenegro, local
residents say, joining the leader of his party, Zoran Djindjic, who
has been accused of being a traitor by the state-run media, but not
indicted. By Steven Erlanger.
