   Bush, in his first term as governor, signed legislation allowing
Texans to carry concealed handguns. He also has opposed forcing gun
retailers to include child safety locks on the weapons they sell.
</P>
<P>
   This week, Bush indicated he would sign into law recently
enacted legislation barring local governments in Texas from suing
gun manufacturers. The legislation pre-empted discussions in
Houston about joining other cities in such suits.
</P>
<P>
   Aides to the vice president avoided any direct reference to Bush
as they spoke with reporters while traveling to Houston for a Gore
fund-raising event, his last stop on a three-day campaign trip
before returning to Washington.
</P>
<P>
   When asked if Gore included Bush when he addressed himself to
``leaders everywhere,'' Gore communications director Laura Quinn
said he was referring to ``all leaders.'' Pressed to elaborate, she
replied, ``All means all.''
</P>
<P>
   Gore also called on the Republican-controlled House to approve
legislation that passed the Senate last week _ on his tie-breaking
vote _ requiring background checks on customers at gun shows. ``Now
is the time not to be silent about an issue like that,'' he said.
``Now is the time ... to make it a law of our land.''
</P>
<P>
   Gore's visit to the Greiner school included an in-the-round
question-and-answer session with students, teachers, parents and
local officials of the type frequently used by Gore and President
Clinton during their campaigns in 1992 and 1996.
</P>
<P>
   The students complained to the vice president of too much
violence in movies and on television and the availability of guns
and drugs _ but mostly of parents not spending enough time with
them.
</P>
<P>
   But twice, when questions arose about allowing prayer in
schools, Gore cited federal Education Department guidelines that
limit religious expressions in public schools.
</P>
<P>
   The vice president's response contrasted with his policy
proposal Monday in Atlanta that would provide government subsidies
to religious organizations that deal with social problems.
</P>
<P>
   ENDIT
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
