of centuries-old retouchings, grime, grease and dust, ``The Last
Supper'' has regained astonishing light and clarity as well as
details of the banquet food that had long been forgotten. But it is
also mottled with large beige patches that signal just how much of
the original art work is lost. By Alessandra Stanley.
