<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-KIDS:HOROSCOPE-CLASSACTS-NYTSF </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
STAR STRUCK? CHECK OUT YOUR WEEK 
 FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE 
 FROM THE FORT WORTH STAR-TELEGRAM
</HEADLINE>
  World rights. 
 By Students SARABETH BALON and NICK FOREMAN 
 Copyright 1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
 (Distributed by New York Times Special Features) 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Before finalizing your activities, take time to read the
following horoscope, which is a fun way to plan your week.
</P>
<P>
   GEMINI (May 21 - June 20): Lending a hand in a situation where
it is needed will be a huge help. You may believe that your
assistance to the problem at hand will be minuscule, but it will
mean all the difference in the world. If you see someone in need,
try and offer your support.
</P>
<P>
   CANCER (June 21 - July 22): Do not be in such a hurry to
complete everything on your to-do list. If you choose to rush
around, the work that you finish will not be quality. Make a game
out of the tasks that you need to finish, and the time will begin
to pass faster.
</P>
<P>
   LEO (July 23 - Aug. 22): When you are forced to make a decision
on behalf of a large group of people, you may want to ask what they
would like to see happen. It is always best to consider the
majority, but the majority does not always have everybody's best
interest at heart.
</P>
<P>
   VIRGO (Aug. 23 - Sept. 22): If you get sick, do not be a baby
about it. Nobody wants to hear you complain about every little ache
and pain that is plaguing you. It is also important that you do not
allow the illness to fester inside of you. It will only get worse.
Do something about it.
</P>
<P>
   LIBRA (Sept. 23 - Oct. 22): Your end-of-the-year tests, social
and scholastic, are basically over. Even if they are not, they will
be some of the easiest tests you will ever take. You and your new
cutie are going to do fine for a long while, so you do not need to
worry about impressing him or her too much. You're liked for who
you are.
</P>
<P>
   SCORPIO (Oct. 23 - Nov. 21): Make the best of the remaining days
of school. Take your yearbook and have all of your friends sign it;
you do not want to realize that you have left someone out of it.
You could use a little help on your tan, so spend time out in the
sun. All the big parties are heading your way, and you do not want
to be stuck with a farmer's tan. Make a date out of tanning in your
back yard. It will be cute.
</P>
<P>
   SAGITTARIUS (Nov. 22 - Dec. 21): To you, what may seem to be
obvious may be extremely deep this week. Your brain will be working
overtime. You will need a couple of minutes to think out a problem
that will face you this weekend. Take into consideration your
parents' input and listen to them. They have been through what you
have, and then some.
</P>
<P>
   CAPRICORN (Dec. 22 - Jan. 19): Last week you were presented with
a surprise. This week you may not be so lucky. It may even feel as
if you are stuck in the doldrums for a while, but do not be scared;
summer is almost here. You will have plenty of time to get rowdy,
hyper and even a little goofy once school has let out. Start
counting down by the minute.
</P>
<P>
   AQUARIUS (Jan. 20 - Feb. 18): You might feel something is
missing. For some reason, you have been getting less and less
sleep, because you are missing something. It's something you
haven't given a lot of thought to. You will gain a new appreciation
for the small things. They are what make life so interesting.
</P>
<P>
   PISCES (Feb. 19 - March 20): It is too easy to get sidetracked
when you think about the summer. It is even easier to completely
give up and blow off the tests and homework. Do not do that. What
you do now could affect what classes and teachers you have next
year. Hold off on that hot date and cram for your tests. A big
reward awaits!
</P>
<P>
   ARIES (March 21 - April 19): This week, you are all about fun
activities. Make it a point to take the initiative in your group of
friends to try something new. It is always good to have a variety
of things to do on any given free day, and the stories that come
with the excitement are usually quite humorous.
</P>
<P>
   TAURUS (April 20 - May 20): You and your friends have been
changing before each other's eyes. Change is not bad, but you must
learn how to adapt to it. It may be a good idea to have a little
bit of brooding time. Share with each other the exciting events of
your lives.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &UR; -0- &QL; 
 &UR; Copyright 1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram &QL; 
 &UR; (Distributed by New York Times Special Features) &QL;
</P>
