<P>
   COMMENTARY (``k'' category)
</P>
<P>
   THOMPSON-COLUMN (Washington) _ Bill Clinton may be right in his
reluctance to send American ground forces to fight in Kosovo. But
the impression he conveyed in initially refusing to even consider
that option was one of a president afraid to use the full power of
the United States to defeat an evil dictator who is systematically
killing and uprooting hundreds of thousands of people. By ROBERT E.
THOMPSON. (Already filed.)
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
