-- How do you communicate with those who do not email? Go to
Letterpost.com, type a letter, and the folks at the other end will
print it out, put it in an envelope and plop it in a mailbox for
delivery by an old fashioned mailman. ``A substantial number of
people, like my parents' generation, will never get E-mail,'' says
the website's founder, Donal O'Mahony, a computer scientist on
sabbatical from Trinity College in Dublin who is now a visiting
scholar at Stanford University. (Norman Y. Lono/New York Times
Photo)
</P>
