<P>
   (NYT13) NEW YORK -- May 26, 1999 -- ADV. FOR SUN., MAY 30 --
ANASTASIA-BALLET-1, 5-26 -- Viviana Durante, who will dance the
title role in ``Anastasia'' this week with American Ballet Theater.
The ballet - set to music by Tchaikovsky - depicts some of the
dramatic, often harshly contrasting events that the woman who
claimed she was Anastasia might have lived through in the days
before and after the Czar's family was executed in 1918. (Nicole
Bengiveno/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT12) NEW YORK -- May 26, 1999 -- ADV. FOR SUN., MAY 30 --
JAZZ-IMPRESSARIOS, 5-26 -- George Wein, seated, and Michael Dorf at
the New York Times recently. Wein and Dorf - impresarios of this
year's JVC Jazz Festival and the Bell Atlantic Jazz Festival,
respectively - have been butting heads for 11 years. ``I can't
understand the new technology and things like that,'' says Wein,
73, who produced 37 music festivals around the world in 1998.
``Jazz is perfectly suited for the Internet because it is a little
more intelligent,'' says Dorf, 37, who runs a club and a record
label. (Jeffrey A. Salter/New York Times Photo)
</P>
