<P>
   ATTENTION EDITORS: The following photos are part of tonight's
New York Times Photo Package, moving 05/26/99. Photo clients will
automatically receive these photos via AP's PhotoExpress or may
download them from either the Wieck Photo Database in Dallas at
972-392-0888 or from NYTPhotos on Newscom at 305-448-8411.
Non-clients can make individual purchases by calling (888) 603-1036
or 212-556-4204.
</P>
<P>
   (NYT31) UNDATED -- May 26, 1999 -- Y2K-CONTINGENCY, 5-26 --
After months of weighing options, businesses and governments are
now being forced to decide how much they will invest in preparing
for year 2000 computer problems, and suddenly contingency planning
has moved to the top of many companies' agendas. Preparations are
likely to include the scheduling of more employees than normal to
be on duty in the weeks before and after New Year's, so that a
company can fall back on nonelectronic methods of business. (Tony
Cenicola/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT30) UNDATED -- May 26, 1999 -- GORE-CAMPAIGN, 5-26 -- Former
Gov. Mario Cuomo of New York, right, says the best thing for Vice
Presi dent Al Gore, center, in his campaign for president, would be
if Hillary Rodham Clinton stays put and does not run for the Senate
from New York. But his son Andrew Cuomo, left, the Secretary of
Housing and Urban Development, says the best thing for Gore's
campaign would be if Mrs. Clinton runs for the Senate. The dueling
Cuomos mirror a larger, public quarrel that is increasingly
consuming prominent Democrats. (Paul Hosefros, left, Bita Honarvar,
Cox News Service, center, Frances Roberts/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT29) MILAN, Italy -- May 26, 1999 -- LAST-SUPPER-2, 5-26 --
Reporters and art experts gather around the unveiling of Leonardo
da Vinci's 1498 masterpiece ``The Last Supper'' in Santa Maria
delle Grazie church after a major restoration which lasted over 20
years. Friday will be the public's first chance to see the painting
unencumbered by scaffolding, easels and equipment. (James Hill/New
York Times Photo) LITE
