<P>
   (NYT24) SPARTANBURG, S.C. -- May 26, 1999 -- SC-HOMEMADE-CD,
5-26 -- Baker Maultsby in a Wal-Mart parking lot in Spartanburg. If
there is anything to be gleaned from Maultsby's homemade CD,
``Bingo  &QC;  Sin,'' which boasts songs about
Wal-Marts, high school delinquents and greasy-food joints, it is
how permeable the line can be these days between brand-name culture
and semi-professional culture. ``People don't know it's not a real
record,'' he says. (Wade Spees/New York Times Photo)
