<P>
   (NYT23) NEW YORK -- May 26, 1999 -- BOOK-TALK, 5-26 -- Elisabeth
Schmitz, editor and success story at Grove/Atlantic. She edits 8 to
10 books a year, and besides being a senior editor is the director
of subsidiary rights. ``At a bigger house I'd probably dump
rights,'' says Ms. Schmitz, 35. ``But everyone wears another hat
here, and anyway rights keeps me in touch with what's going on with
other publishers, and lets me deal with other editors.'' (Sara
Krulwich/New York Times Photo)
</P>
