<P>
   (NYT27) CAMBRIDGE, Mass. -- May 26, 1999 -- AUTHOR-PIPES-BOS,
5-26 -- Richard Pipes' new book, ``Freedom and Property,'' is a
departure for the Harvard historian and one of the West's foremost
authorities on the Kremlin. A study of the connection between
political liberty and private ownership, it devotes only one of its
five sections to Russian history. ``In general, almost everything
that has been written in the field (of Soviet history) since the
'60s has been quite wrong,'' says Pipes, 75. (Wendy Maeda/Boston
Globe Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT26) MORINI, Albania -- May 26, 1999 -- KOSOVO-ALBANIA, 5-26
-- An exhausted and dehydrated ethnic Albanian refugee, who had
just crossed into Albania from neighboring Kosovo, is comforted on
a bus taking the refugees to a nearby camp on Wednesday. More than
300 refugees crossed into Albania Wednesday. (Tyler Hicks/New York
Times Photo)
</P>
