Rep. Christopher Shays, right, huddles with his Rep. Greg Ganske
before a press conference on campaign finance reform, Wednesday. A
small group of Republicans broke with their party and signed a
petition to force a vote on campaign finance overhaul. Shays made a
frontal assault on Rep. Tom DeLay, the Republican whip, calling it
a struggle for the soul of the Republican party. Shays accused
Delay of threatening to fund a primary challenge in his district.
(Stephen Crowley/New York Times Photo)
