<HEADLINE>
DODGERS VS. CINCINNATI
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By BRIAN DOHN  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
 
__ Time: 9:35 a.m., at Cinergy Field. 
__ TV/Radio: No TV; KXTA-AM (1150-AM), KWKW-AM (1330 Spanish). 
__ Matchup: Dodgers right-hander Ismael Valdes (4-2, 3.77 ERA) was
one of the pitchers most affected by Tuesday's firing of pitching
coach Charlie Hough, and he makes the start as the Dodgers and Reds
wrap up their three-game series. ``He gave me confidence. I worked
hard, but I really liked the guy,'' Valdes said. He's coming off
his shortest outing of the season in which he allowed six runs
(four earned) on six hits in 41/3 innings against St. Louis. Valdes
is 9-4 in his past 13 decisions dating back to last season. The
Reds counter with righty Pete Harnisch (4-4, 3.16). He's 2-0 with a
1.04 ERA in his past two starts and is 6-4 with a 2.84 ERA in his
career against the Dodgers. 

