</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-RAC-BELMONT-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
2000 RACES TO BE RUN AT CHURCHILL DOWNS 
</HEADLINE>
  (lb) 
 By JOSEPH DURSO   
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Breeders' Cup announced Wednesday that it would run its
first series of championship races in 2000 at Churchill Downs on
Nov. 4. And it said that Belmont Park would most likely be the site
of the 2001 races.
</P>
<P>
   This will mark the fifth time that Churchill Downs will be the
host to the Breeders' Cup. The track, the home of the Kentucky
Derby, was the scene of the cup races in 1988, 1991, 1994 and 1998.
</P>
<P>
   The 2000 races were originally scheduled for Santa Anita, but
the track withdrew its bid to complete renovations.
</P>
<P>
   This year's races will be at Gulfstream Park on Nov. 6.
</P>
<P>
   ``We have received considerable interest from the New York
Racing Association to host the cup in 2001,'' D.G. Van Clief Jr.,
president of the Breeders' Cup, said, ``and we will work toward
that goal in the coming months.'' He expressed interest in
conducting the Breeders' Cup at Belmont on the last Saturday in
October, with daylight time in effect.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
