<SLUG> BC-NY-GUN-SUIT-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
JUDGE BACKS RULING THAT GUN MAKERS MUST PAY SHOOTING VICTIM
</HEADLINE>
   (rk) 
 By ANDY NEWMAN   
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ A federal judge upheld a precedent-setting verdict
Wednesday against three gun makers, ordering them to pay more than
$522,000 in damages to the family of a Queens teen-ager who was
shot and severely wounded with an illegally obtained handgun.
</P>
<P>
   The jury in the lawsuit, filed in U.S. District Court in
Brooklyn, had found in February that the gun makers were
collectively liable for the shooting, even though the gun used in
the shooting was never identified. The manufacturers were
responsible, the jury found, because they had oversupplied states
that had weak gun laws, which led to illegal sales in states with
stricter regulations, like New York.
</P>
<P>
   In his ruling Wednesday, Judge Jack B. Weinstein dismissed a
motion by the gun makers _ the Beretta USA Corp., Taurus
International Manufacturing Inc. and American Arms Inc. _ to
overturn the verdict. The three companies all make .25-caliber guns
like the one that was used to shoot the teen-ager, Steven Fox, in
the head.
</P>
<P>
   The gun makers had argued that under New York state law, a
manufacturer has no legal duty to refrain from selling a legal
product in accordance with the law. They had also said that the
jury had disregarded the judge's instruction that the plaintiff had
to prove what year the gun had been sold.
</P>
<P>
   A lawyer for Beretta, Lawrence G. Keane, said the company would
appeal.
</P>
<P>
   Beretta must pay Fox and his family $241,200, Taurus must pay
$272,000, and American Arms, Inc., must pay $9,200. The amounts
were determined by the gun makers' market share of .25-caliber
guns.
</P>
<P>
   The judge dismissed the cases of 12 other firearms makers that
the jury had found negligent in their marketing practices. Since
the jury did not award damages against those 12, he said, the
plaintiffs failed overall.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
